From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 20:45:00 +0800
Subject: Normalize GPU capability values to match NVIDIA RTX 4090 hardware

Sets GPU capabilities to consistent NVIDIA RTX 4090-class values when
PureCloak noise is enabled. This prevents capability-based fingerprinting
where different GPU hardware reports different supported values.

Normalizes:
- max_msaa_samples → "16" (RTX 4090 supports 16x MSAA)

Depends on patch #31 (GL renderer/vendor/version normalization) for
the PureCloak buildflag and seed includes.

---
 gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc b/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc
--- a/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc
+++ b/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc
@@ -682,6 +682,14 @@ bool CollectGraphicsInfoGL(GPUInfo* gpu_info, gl::GLDisplay* display) {
   if (!active_gpu_identified)
     IdentifyActiveGPU(gpu_info);
 
+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
+  // PureCloak: normalize GPU capability values to match real hardware
+  // (NVIDIA RTX 4090-class) when noise is enabled.
+  if (purecloak::PureCloakSeed::GetInstance()->noise_enabled()) {
+    gpu_info->max_msaa_samples = "16";
+  }
+#endif
+
   return true;
 }
 
